00:13:46.549 --> 00:13:47.308
Yes sir.
 

00:13:47.308 --> 00:13:47.870
Student:  What letter is
that?

00:13:47.870 --> 00:13:49.120
Prof: Galatians 3:28.
 

00:13:49.120 --> 00:13:54.044
This has been an argument,
this is why I'm talking about

00:13:54.044 --> 00:13:56.299
the stuff--
those of you who are writing

00:13:56.299 --> 00:13:57.779
papers this week need to talk
about,

00:13:57.779 --> 00:13:59.269
but notice this is complex.
 

00:13:59.269 --> 00:14:03.442
You've got Galatians 3:28 that
looks like an egalitarian

00:14:03.442 --> 00:14:06.912
statement,
except a very famous biblical

00:14:06.912 --> 00:14:12.134
scholar wrote an article arguing
that Galatians 3:28 is not an

00:14:12.134 --> 00:14:17.100
egalitarian statement because
Paul was talking about in the

00:14:17.100 --> 00:14:22.341
resurrection human beings--
Christians will be androgynes,

00:14:22.341 --> 00:14:25.928
that they'll be male/female
combinations,

00:14:25.928 --> 00:14:31.241
and in that male/female
combination the masculinity is

00:14:31.241 --> 00:14:36.955
still superior to femininity
even in the androgyne body of

00:14:36.955 --> 00:14:39.058
the resurrection.
 

00:14:39.058 --> 00:14:43.100
Is Galatians 3:28 an
egalitarian statement by Paul?

00:14:43.100 --> 00:14:44.389
Some people say yes.
 

00:14:44.389 --> 00:14:47.149
Is it not an egalitarian
statement by Paul?

00:14:47.149 --> 00:14:49.830
I say it's not.
 

00:14:49.830 --> 00:14:52.658
That's a complicated argument
also.

00:14:52.658 --> 00:14:57.139
If Galatians 3:28 is an
